HEADWORD: Atticism
<hw>At"ti*cism</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>A favoring of, or attachment to, the
Athenians.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The style and idiom of the Greek language, used by
the Athenians; a concise and elegant expression.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Atticize</ent>⟦br⟧
